[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scotland claims Thursday's hottest UK spots as the Indian summer continues

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland has again had the warmest places in the UK with temperatures rising to 22.7C in Braemar, according to the latest figures.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
At Balmoral 21.5C was recorded and 20.9C at Charterhall, Berwickshire, and 20.8C at Aviemore and 20.3C at Drumnadrochit near Loch Ness.
The temperatures followed 23.3C recorded at Braemar on Wednesday and 23.2C in Aboyne on Tuesday.
Updated temperatures for Thursday are expected later.
